  "local_port": 50148,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I submit feedback to Quora?",
  "response": "Submitting feedback to Quora is a straightforward process. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### 1. **Through the Quora Website:**\n   - **Log in to Your Account:** Go to Quora and log in to your account.\n   - **Access the Help Center:** Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner, then select **\"Help Center\"** from the dropdown menu.\n   - **Submit Feedback:** In the Help Center, you\u2019ll find an option to **\"Submit Feedback\"**. Click on it.\n   - **Fill Out the Form:** You\u2019ll be directed to a feedback form. Fill out the form with your feedback, including details about the issue or suggestion you have. Be as specific as possible.\n   - **Submit:** Once you\u2019ve completed the form, click **\"Submit\"** to send your feedback to Quora.\n\n### 2. **Through the Quora Mobile App:**\n   - **Open the App:** Open the Quora app on your mobile device.\n   - **Go to Settings:** Tap on your profile picture in the bottom-right corner, then go to **\"Settings\"**.\n   - **Help & Support:** Scroll down and tap on **\"Help & Support\"**.\n   - **Submit Feedback:** Tap on **\"Submit Feedback\"** and fill out the form that appears. Include details about your issue or suggestion.\n   - **Submit:** Tap **\"Submit\"** to send your feedback.\n\n### 3. **Via Email:**\n   - You can also email your feedback directly to Quora at **feedback@quora.com**. Make sure to include as much detail as possible in your email.\n\n### 4. **Reporting Specific Content:**\n   - If your feedback is related to specific content (e.g., a post, comment, or user), you can report it directly:\n     - Click on the **three dots (\u2022\u2022\u2022)** next to the content.\n     - Select **\"Report\"** and follow the prompts to explain your concern.\n\n### Tips for Effective Feedback:\n   - **Be Clear and Concise:** Clearly describe the issue or suggestion.\n   - **Provide Examples:** If possible, include examples or screenshots to illustrate your point.\n   - **Be Polite:** Constructive feedback is more likely to be well-received.\n\nQuora\u2019s team reviews feedback regularly and uses it to improve the platform.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
